== How to run

1. bundle install
2. bundle exec rake db:migrate
3. bundle exec rake db:seed
4. bundle exec rake db:admin:create
3. rails server

Install DevKit if OS is Windows
https://github.com/oneclick/rubyinstaller/wiki/Development-Kit

Install mysql2 gem on Windows
gem install mysql2  -v='0.2.8' -- '--with-mysql-lib="D:\Program Files\MySQL\MySQL Server 5.5\lib" --with-mysql-include="D:\Program Files\MySQL\MySQL Server 5.5\include"
then copy libmysql.dll to RUBY_PATH/bin or add it to Path

if you specify root user to mysql then run

bundle exec rake db:create
for db creation

bundle exec rake db:drop
for db drop